    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for Model Risk Level 3. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) reflects the single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol and is considered acceptable given the strong inter-laboratory reproducibility and the conservative nature of the standard test. All three primary QoIs satisfy the pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, relative difference <10%). The credibility assessment team concludes that the FEA modeling framework is sufficiently credible for the stated COU. Note: this package conforms to ProfileMinimal; the signature workflow is pending and no digital signature has been applied. Structural integrity of the package cannot be cryptographically verified until signature is appended.",
